column1255: It's not the task of the scissors really... This sentence only works for me in a specific interpretation where you want to emphasise the importance of the scissors for some reason.
column1256: The sentence is natural, but again the punctuation is awkward, if not plainly wrong: these are two sentences that should be separated not by a comma, but by a full stop and then a capital letter.
column1258: I would say 'van waar' not 'vanaf waar', but that might be my southern Dutch dialectal influence ;-)
column1259: The coordination makes it weird for me, it would be improved if it ended with 'om een toespraak te houden'.
column1262: It's not really natural for me because the reason 'omdat hij...' should come first.
column1264: Again, please correct the missing punctuation mark: there should be a comma between 'beschikte' and 'was'.
column1266: 'op het werk' is very weird in this sentence: where else would you have lunch if you're having it in your canteen?
column1268: The definite article in 'het stadion' is weird for me, because I have no idea which station is meant. Otherwise the sentences sounds perfectly natural to me.
column1269: 'opgesomd staan' is weird for me. 'was opgesomd' would make this sentence perfectly fine for me.
column1270: There is no full stop at the end of the sentence. Missing punctuation is a bit annoying and sometimes misleading. But perhaps that's part of your goal?
column1271: I don't have a dog, I can't relate to this ;-)
column1273: 'ene' really degrades the sentence in my view. It would be much better without it.
column1278: Again, these are two separate sentences. It sounds unnatural to repeat 'the table' at the end.
column1280: This reading/sentence is only possible if the conductor is (constrastively) focussed.
column1281: 'maar' and 'slechts' don't work together at all: choose one!
column1283: The postpositioned PP 'naar de vijver' is OK, but it would be much better together with 'park'.
column1291: Sentences are OK and natural, but only if they are separated into two sentences.
